        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): upgrade single newlines to double newlines for post+md rendering (fixes #97074)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #97074.\n\nWhen OpenClaw sends messages to Feishu via `msg_type: post` with `tag: md`, **single newline characters (`\\n`) are rendered as plain spaces** by the Feishu IM API. This causes paragraphs to appear mashed together, making long messages difficult to read.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nFeishu's `post` + `tag: md` rendering treats a single `\\n` as a soft break (space), not a line break. Only `\\n\\n` (double newline) triggers a proper paragraph break. The fix adds `normalizeFeishuNewlines()` which upgrades single `\\n` to `\\n\\n` before the text enters the post payload, while preserving code blocks and existing `\\n\\n` sequences.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `extensions/feishu/src/send.ts`: Added `normalizeFeishuNewlines()` function and wired it into `buildFeishuPostMessagePayload` (both send and edit paths benefit automatically).\n- `extensions/feishu/src/send.test.ts`: Added 3 regression tests.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Unit tests:** `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/feishu/src/send.test.ts` — 22/22 passed\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n```\nInput:  \"Hello\\nWorld\"\nOutput: \"Hello\\n\\nWorld\"\n✅ Single newline upgraded to double newline\n\nInput:  \"Para 1\\n\\nPara 2\"\nOutput: \"Para 1\\n\\nPara 2\"\n✅ Existing double newlines preserved unchanged\n\nInput:  \"Before\\n```\\ncode\\nblock\\n```\\nAfter\"\nOutput: \"Before\\n\\n```\\ncode\\nblock\\n```\\n\\nAfter\"\n✅ Single newlines outside code blocks upgraded\n✅ Code block internal newlines preserved\n```\n\n- [x] AI-assisted",
        "branch": "fix/issue-97074-feishu-newline",
